definitions.definition: The scientific study of the origin and evolution of a word's semantic meaning across time, including its constituent morphemes and phonemes.
The entire catalogue of meanings that a word, morpheme, or sign has carried throughout its history.
examples: Although written the same, the words lead (the metal) and lead (the verb) have totally different etymologies .

definitions.definition: An account of the origin and historical development of a word as presented in a dictionary or the like.
The direct origin of a name, as in who someone was named after.
